{"data":[{"type":"questionAttempts","id":"17599473","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/questionAttempts/17599473"},"attributes":{"position":0,"marks":1,"score":0,"answeredAt":"2025-09-30T11:54:51+09:30","options":[1],"response":null,"finalizedAt":"2025-09-30T11:54:51+09:30"},"relationships":{"user":{"data":{"type":"users","id":"50098"}},"questionSession":{"data":null},"session":{"data":null},"question":{"data":{"type":"questions","id":"15569"}},"bookmark":{"data":null}}}],"included":[{"type":"questions","id":"15569","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/questions/15569"},"relationships":{"item":{"data":{"type":"items","id":"8260"}},"activeRevision":{"data":{"type":"questionRevisions","id":"70161"}}}},{"type":"items","id":"8260","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/items/8260"},"attributes":{"contentType":"question"},"relationships":{"content":{"data":{"type":"questions","id":"15569"}},"activeRevision":{"data":{"type":"itemRevisions","id":"55624"}},"tags":{"data":[{"type":"tags","id":"67"},{"type":"tags","id":"71"},{"type":"tags","id":"74"},{"type":"tags","id":"4929"},{"type":"tags","id":"4942"},{"type":"tags","id":"7607"}]},"contributions":{"data":[{"type":"contributions","id":"19957"},{"type":"contributions","id":"19960"}]}},"meta":{"canRevise":false,"canManage":false,"canDelete":false}},{"type":"questionRevisions","id":"70161","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/questionRevisions/70161"},"attributes":{"stem":"\u003Cp\u003EThyroid binding globulin (TBG) is the primary transport protein for thyroid hormones in blood. Its levels can be affected by various hormonal states including pregnancy.\u003C/p\u003E","stemQuestion":"Which one of the following hormones increases thyroid binding globulin synthesis in the liver?","responseType":"sba","marks":1,"options":["Androgenic steroids","Glucocorticoids","Oestrogen","Growth hormone","Progesterone"],"correctOptions":[2],"correctResponses":null,"explanation":"\u003Cp\u003E\u003Cstrong\u003EAndrogenic steroids\u003C/strong\u003E decrease hepatic TBG synthesis and therefore lower plasma TBG levels. \u003Cstrong\u003EGlucocorticoids\u003C/strong\u003E have minimal effect on TBG production. \u003Cstrong\u003EOestrogen\u003C/strong\u003E stimulates hepatic TBG synthesis, which explains the elevated TBG levels seen during pregnancy and in people taking oestrogen-containing medications. \u003Cstrong\u003EGrowth hormone\u003C/strong\u003E does not significantly influence TBG production. \u003Cstrong\u003EProgesterone\u003C/strong\u003E has minimal direct effects on TBG synthesis.\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cp\u003EUnderstanding TBG regulation is clinically important because changes in TBG levels affect the interpretation of thyroid function tests. During pregnancy, increased TBG leads to higher total thyroid hormone levels while free hormone levels remain normal.\u003C/p\u003E","optionExplanations":null,"learningPoints":["Oestrogen increases thyroid binding globulin (TBG) synthesis in the liver","TBG is the main transport protein for thyroid hormones in blood, carrying about 75% of circulating thyroid hormones","Elevated TBG during pregnancy can affect interpretation of thyroid function tests"],"references":["Santin AP, Furlanetto TW. Role of estrogen in thyroid function and growth regulation. J Thyroid Res. 2011;2011:875125. doi: 10.4061/2011/875125. Epub 2011 May 4. PMID: 21687614; PMCID: PMC3113168.","Melmed, S., Polonsky, K. S., Larsen, P. R., \u0026 Kronenberg, H. M. (2015). Williams textbook of endocrinology E-Book. Elsevier Health Sciences","Clark, O. H., Duh, Q. Y., Kebebew, E., Gosnell, J. E., \u0026 Shen, W. T. (Eds.). (2016). Textbook of endocrine surgery. JP Medical Ltd","Young, W. F. (2011). Netter\u0027s Endocrine System: Netter Collection of Medical Illustrations: Endocrine System E-book. Elsevier Health Sciences","Wass, J. A., \u0026 Stewart, P. M. (Eds.). (2011). Oxford textbook of endocrinology and diabetes. Oxford University Press, USA"]},"relationship